{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":874,"text":"I experienced my first coup d'état at the age of four."},{"time":5125,"text":"Because of the coup d'état,"},{"time":6835,"text":"my family had to leave my native home of Ghana"},{"time":9962,"text":"and move to the Gambia."},{"time":12178,"text":"As luck would have it,"},{"time":13899,"text":"six months after we arrived,"},{"time":15632,"text":"they too had a military coup."},{"time":18703,"text":"I vividly remember being woken\nup in the middle of the night"},{"time":21121,"text":"and gathering the few belongings we could"},{"time":23348,"text":"and walking for about two hours"},{"time":26297,"text":"to a safe house."},{"time":28343,"text":"For a week, we slept under our beds"},{"time":31175,"text":"because we were worried that bullets\nmight fly through the window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35956,"text":"Then, at the age of eight,"},{"time":38138,"text":"we moved to Botswana."},{"time":40265,"text":"This time, it was different."},{"time":42458,"text":"There were no coups."},{"time":44292,"text":"Everything worked. Great education."},{"time":47335,"text":"They had such good infrastructure\nthat even at the time they had"},{"time":50310,"text":"a fiber-optic telephone system,"},{"time":52211,"text":"long before it had reached Western countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57466,"text":"The only thing they didn't have"},{"time":59349,"text":"is that they didn't have"},{"time":60679,"text":"their own national television station,"},{"time":63329,"text":"and so I remember watching"},{"time":65220,"text":"TV from neighboring South Africa,"},{"time":67705,"text":"and watching Nelson Mandela in jail"},{"time":70326,"text":"being offered a chance to come out"},{"time":72621,"text":"if he would give up the apartheid struggle."},{"time":75501,"text":"But he didn't. He refused to do that"},{"time":76616,"text":"until he actually achieved his objective"},{"time":78464,"text":"of freeing South Africa from apartheid."},{"time":81676,"text":"And I remember feeling how just one good leader"},{"time":85709,"text":"could make such a big difference in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90557,"text":"Then at the age of 12,"},{"time":92830,"text":"my family sent me to high school in Zimbabwe."},{"time":96170,"text":"Initially, this too was amazing:"},{"time":99747,"text":"growing economy, excellent infrastructure,"},{"time":104933,"text":"and it seemed like it was a model"},{"time":106969,"text":"for economic development in Africa."},{"time":109658,"text":"I graduated from high school in Zimbabwe"},{"time":111649,"text":"and I went off to college."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113070,"text":"Six years later, I returned to the country."},{"time":117161,"text":"Everything was different."},{"time":119145,"text":"It had shattered into pieces."},{"time":122396,"text":"Millions of people had emigrated,"},{"time":125606,"text":"the economy was in a shambles,"},{"time":127413,"text":"and it seemed all of a sudden that 30 years"},{"time":129004,"text":"of development had been wiped out."},{"time":131889,"text":"How could a country go so bad so fast?"},{"time":135377,"text":"Most people would agree"},{"time":136990,"text":"that it's all because of leadership."},{"time":139178,"text":"One man, President Robert Mugabe,"},{"time":142958,"text":"is almost single-handedly responsible"},{"time":144168,"text":"for having destroyed this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147515,"text":"Now, all these experiences of living in different"},{"time":149244,"text":"parts of Africa growing up"},{"time":151675,"text":"did two things to me."},{"time":153497,"text":"The first is it made me fall in love with Africa."},{"time":157776,"text":"Everywhere I went,"},{"time":159699,"text":"I experienced the wonderful beauty of our continent"},{"time":162377,"text":"and saw the resilience and the spirit of our people,"},{"time":165534,"text":"and at the time, I realized that I wanted to dedicate"},{"time":167461,"text":"the rest of my life to making this continent great."},{"time":172242,"text":"But I also realized that making Africa great"},{"time":174144,"text":"would require addressing this issue of leadership."},{"time":177461,"text":"You see, all these countries I lived in,"},{"time":179632,"text":"the coups d'état"},{"time":181624,"text":"and the corruption I'd seen in Ghana and Gambia"},{"time":184683,"text":"and in Zimbabwe,"},{"time":187405,"text":"contrasted with the wonderful examples I had seen"},{"time":191858,"text":"in Botswana and in South \nAfrica of good leadership."},{"time":196412,"text":"It made me realize that Africa would rise or fall"},{"time":200495,"text":"because of the quality of our leaders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204174,"text":"Now, one might think, of course,"},{"time":206423,"text":"leadership matters everywhere."},{"time":209191,"text":"But if there's one thing you take\naway from my talk today, it is this:"},{"time":213421,"text":"In Africa, more than anywhere else in the world,"},{"time":216550,"text":"the difference that just one good leader can make"},{"time":219876,"text":"is much greater than anywhere \nelse, and here's why."},{"time":223435,"text":"It's because in Africa, we have weak institutions,"},{"time":226225,"text":"like the judiciary, the constitution,"},{"time":228903,"text":"civil society and so forth."},{"time":232094,"text":"So here's a general rule of thumb that I believe in:"},{"time":235944,"text":"When societies have strong institutions,"},{"time":238711,"text":"the difference that one good\nleader can make is limited,"},{"time":241973,"text":"but when you have weak institutions,"},{"time":244180,"text":"then just one good leader"},{"time":245910,"text":"can make or break that country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248058,"text":"Let me make it a bit more concrete."},{"time":251366,"text":"You become the president of the United States."},{"time":254415,"text":"You think, \"Wow, I've arrived."},{"time":256687,"text":"I'm the most powerful man in the world.\""},{"time":259750,"text":"So you decide, perhaps let me pass a law."},{"time":263436,"text":"All of a sudden, Congress taps you on the shoulder"},{"time":264978,"text":"and says, \"No, no, no, no, no, you can't do that.\""},{"time":268111,"text":"You say, \"Let me try this way.\""},{"time":270820,"text":"The Senate comes and says, \"Uh-uh,"},{"time":272273,"text":"we don't think you can do that.\""},{"time":275101,"text":"You say, perhaps, \"Let me print some money."},{"time":277744,"text":"I think the economy needs a stimulus.\""},{"time":280399,"text":"The central bank governor will think you're crazy."},{"time":281894,"text":"You might get impeached for that."},{"time":285000,"text":"But if you become the president of Zimbabwe,"},{"time":287307,"text":"and you say, \"You know, I really like this job."},{"time":290440,"text":"I think I'd like to stay in it forever.\"\n(Laughter)"},{"time":295225,"text":"Well, you just can."},{"time":298070,"text":"You decide you want to print money."},{"time":300550,"text":"You call the central bank governor and you say,"},{"time":302453,"text":"\"Please double the money supply.\""},{"time":304785,"text":"He'll say, \"Okay, yes, sir,"},{"time":306226,"text":"is there anything else I can do for you?\""},{"time":309770,"text":"This is the power that African leaders have,"},{"time":313609,"text":"and this is why they make the most difference"},{"time":317127,"text":"on the continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319581,"text":"The good news is that"},{"time":321626,"text":"the quality of leadership in Africa has been improving."},{"time":324464,"text":"We've had three generations \nof leaders, in my mind."},{"time":327206,"text":"Generation one are those who appeared"},{"time":329434,"text":"in the '50s and '60s."},{"time":330976,"text":"These are people like Kwame Nkrumah of Ghana"},{"time":333414,"text":"and Julius Nyerere of Tanzania."},{"time":335827,"text":"The legacy they left is that they\nbrought independence to Africa."},{"time":338432,"text":"They freed us from colonialism,"},{"time":339737,"text":"and let's give them credit for that."},{"time":342121,"text":"They were followed by generation two."},{"time":345133,"text":"These are people that brought nothing"},{"time":347183,"text":"but havoc to Africa."},{"time":349320,"text":"Think warfare, corruption, human rights abuses."},{"time":352750,"text":"This is the stereotype of \nthe typical African leader"},{"time":354783,"text":"that we typically think of:"},{"time":356178,"text":"Mobutu Sese Seko from Zaire,"},{"time":358184,"text":"Sani Abacha from Nigeria."},{"time":360565,"text":"The good news is that most of\nthese leaders have moved on,"},{"time":363741,"text":"and they were replaced by generation three."},{"time":365845,"text":"These are people like the late Nelson Mandela"},{"time":368161,"text":"and most of the leaders that we see in Africa today,"},{"time":370175,"text":"like Paul Kagame and so forth."},{"time":372852,"text":"Now these leaders are by no means perfect,"},{"time":375960,"text":"but the one thing they have done is that they have"},{"time":377605,"text":"cleaned up much of the mess of generation two."},{"time":380603,"text":"They've stopped the fighting,"},{"time":382061,"text":"and I call them the stabilizer generation."},{"time":385160,"text":"They're much more accountable to their people,"},{"time":387110,"text":"they've improved macroeconomic policies,"},{"time":390305,"text":"and we are seeing for the first time"},{"time":392240,"text":"Africa's growing, and in \nfact it's the second fastest"},{"time":394580,"text":"growing economic region in the world."},{"time":396425,"text":"So these leaders are by no means perfect,"},{"time":398591,"text":"but they are by and large"},{"time":399923,"text":"the best leaders we've seen in the last 50 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404749,"text":"So where to from here?"},{"time":407628,"text":"I believe that the next generation"},{"time":409844,"text":"to come after this, generation four,"},{"time":412476,"text":"has a unique opportunity"},{"time":415009,"text":"to transform the continent."},{"time":417564,"text":"Specifically, they can do two things"},{"time":419408,"text":"that previous generations have not done."},{"time":421534,"text":"The first thing they need to do"},{"time":423716,"text":"is they need to create prosperity for the continent."},{"time":426144,"text":"Why is prosperity so important?"},{"time":428031,"text":"Because none of the previous generations"},{"time":429714,"text":"have been able to tackle this issue of poverty."},{"time":432394,"text":"Africa today"},{"time":433710,"text":"has the fastest growing population in the world,"},{"time":436540,"text":"but also is the poorest."},{"time":439241,"text":"By 2030, Africa will have a\nlarger workforce than China,"},{"time":442918,"text":"and by 2050, it will have the\nlargest workforce in the world."},{"time":446720,"text":"One billion people will need jobs in Africa,"},{"time":449252,"text":"so if we don't grow our economies fast enough,"},{"time":451626,"text":"we're sitting on a ticking time bomb,"},{"time":454073,"text":"not just for Africa but for the entire world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457605,"text":"Let me show you an example"},{"time":459743,"text":"of one person who is living up to this legacy"},{"time":461449,"text":"of creating prosperity: Laetitia."},{"time":464212,"text":"Laetitia's a young woman from Kenya"},{"time":467203,"text":"who at the age of 13 had to drop out of school"},{"time":469000,"text":"because her family couldn't \nafford to pay fees for her."},{"time":471910,"text":"So she started her own business rearing rabbits,"},{"time":474111,"text":"which happen to be a delicacy in this part of Kenya"},{"time":475710,"text":"that she's from."},{"time":477308,"text":"This business did so well that within a year,"},{"time":479292,"text":"she was employing 15 women"},{"time":481448,"text":"and was able to generate enough income"},{"time":483425,"text":"that she was able to send herself to school,"},{"time":485146,"text":"and through these women"},{"time":486155,"text":"fund another 65 children to go to school."},{"time":488862,"text":"The profits that she generated,"},{"time":490564,"text":"she used that to build a school,"},{"time":492149,"text":"and today she educates"},{"time":493697,"text":"400 children in her community."},{"time":496238,"text":"And she's just turned 18."},{"time":498128,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504857,"text":"Another example is Erick Rajaonary."},{"time":508713,"text":"Erick comes from the island of Madagascar."},{"time":511797,"text":"Now, Erick realized that agriculture"},{"time":514596,"text":"would be the key to creating jobs"},{"time":516260,"text":"in the rural areas of Madagascar,"},{"time":518319,"text":"but he also realized that fertilizer was a very"},{"time":520265,"text":"expensive input for most farmers in Madagascar."},{"time":523596,"text":"Madagascar has these very special bats"},{"time":526623,"text":"that produce these droppings"},{"time":528207,"text":"that are very high in nutrients."},{"time":530614,"text":"In 2006, Erick quit his job \nas a chartered accountant"},{"time":533989,"text":"and started a company to manufacture"},{"time":535958,"text":"fertilizer from the bat droppings."},{"time":539144,"text":"Today, Erick has built a business"},{"time":541442,"text":"that generates several million dollars of revenue,"},{"time":544283,"text":"and he employs 70 people full time"},{"time":547116,"text":"and another 800 people during the season"},{"time":548994,"text":"when the bats drop their droppings the most."},{"time":551976,"text":"Now, what I like about this story"},{"time":554539,"text":"is that it shows that opportunities \nto create prosperity"},{"time":558421,"text":"can be found almost anywhere."},{"time":560716,"text":"Erick is known as the Batman."},{"time":562770,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":563785,"text":"And who would have thought that you would have"},{"time":565752,"text":"been able to build a multimillion-dollar business"},{"time":568414,"text":"employing so many people just from bat poo?"},{"time":575444,"text":"The second thing that this generation needs to do"},{"time":579395,"text":"is to create our institutions."},{"time":581836,"text":"They need to build these institutions such that we"},{"time":583651,"text":"are never held to ransom again"},{"time":586876,"text":"by a few individuals like Robert Mugabe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591330,"text":"Now, all of this sounds great,"},{"time":594472,"text":"but where are we going to\nget this generation four from?"},{"time":598500,"text":"Do we just sit and hope that they emerge"},{"time":600941,"text":"by chance, or that God gives them to us?"},{"time":604705,"text":"No, I don't think so."},{"time":606458,"text":"It's too important an issue \nfor us to leave it to chance."},{"time":609610,"text":"I believe that we need to create African institutions,"},{"time":612917,"text":"home-grown, that will identify and develop"},{"time":615628,"text":"these leaders in a systematic, practical way."},{"time":619379,"text":"We've been doing this for the last 10 years"},{"time":621030,"text":"through the African Leadership Academy."},{"time":623581,"text":"Laetitia is one of our young leaders."},{"time":626262,"text":"Today, we have 700 of them \nthat are being groomed"},{"time":628670,"text":"for the African continent,"},{"time":630720,"text":"and over the next 50 years,"},{"time":631795,"text":"we expect to create 6,000 of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634789,"text":"But one thing has been troubling me."},{"time":637408,"text":"We would get about 4,000 applications a year"},{"time":639500,"text":"for 100 young leaders that we could take"},{"time":641569,"text":"into this academy,"},{"time":642883,"text":"and so I saw the tremendous hunger that existed"},{"time":644944,"text":"for this leadership training that we're offering."},{"time":647835,"text":"But we couldn't satisfy it."},{"time":650951,"text":"So today, I'm announcing for the first time in public"},{"time":654973,"text":"an extension to this vision for\nthe African Leadership Academy."},{"time":659611,"text":"We're building 25 brand new universities in Africa"},{"time":664718,"text":"that are going to cultivate this next generation"},{"time":666267,"text":"of African leaders."},{"time":668113,"text":"Each campus will have 10,000 leaders at a time"},{"time":671975,"text":"so we'll be educating and developing"},{"time":674201,"text":"250,000 leaders at any given time."},{"time":677015,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684137,"text":"Over the next 50 years, this institution"},{"time":686388,"text":"will create three million transformative leaders"},{"time":688346,"text":"for the continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690379,"text":"My hope is that half of them"},{"time":692620,"text":"will become the entrepreneurs that we need,"},{"time":694172,"text":"who will create these jobs that we need,"},{"time":695995,"text":"and the other half"},{"time":697502,"text":"will go into government"},{"time":699189,"text":"and the nonprofit sector,"},{"time":700388,"text":"and they will build the institutions that we need."},{"time":704010,"text":"But they won't just learn academics."},{"time":707400,"text":"They will also learn how to become leaders,"},{"time":710190,"text":"and they will develop their skills as entrepreneurs."},{"time":712074,"text":"So think of this as Africa's Ivy League,"},{"time":715938,"text":"but instead of getting admitted\nbecause of your SAT scores"},{"time":719220,"text":"or because of how much money you have"},{"time":721101,"text":"or which family you come from,"},{"time":722303,"text":"the main criteria for getting into this university"},{"time":725225,"text":"will be what is the potential that you have"},{"time":727199,"text":"for transforming Africa?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":730461,"text":"But what we're doing is \njust one group of institutions."},{"time":733970,"text":"We cannot transform Africa by ourselves."},{"time":738060,"text":"My hope"},{"time":739762,"text":"is that many, many other home-grown"},{"time":741900,"text":"African institutions will blossom,"},{"time":745318,"text":"and these institutions will all come together"},{"time":747020,"text":"with a common vision of developing"},{"time":749480,"text":"this next generation of African leaders,"},{"time":751363,"text":"generation four,"},{"time":753296,"text":"and they will teach them this common message:"},{"time":755760,"text":"create jobs, build our institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760540,"text":"Nelson Mandela once said,"},{"time":762790,"text":"\"Every now and then,"},{"time":764592,"text":"a generation is called upon to be great."},{"time":767828,"text":"You can be that great generation.\""},{"time":771036,"text":"I believe that if we carefully identify and cultivate"},{"time":774588,"text":"the next generation of African leaders,"},{"time":777561,"text":"then this generation four that is coming up"},{"time":780336,"text":"will be the greatest generation that Africa"},{"time":783768,"text":"and indeed the entire world has ever seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788180,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790212,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}